The paper discusses the analysis of bibliographic records from the Web of Science in communication networks using complex network-based analytical approaches. This falls under the field of scientometrics, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the quantitative analysis of scientific literature. The paper also focuses on emerging topics in internet technology, which can be related to subcategories such as social networks (cs.SI), network infrastructure (cs.NI), system and data security (cs.SD), cyber-physical systems (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR).
